fter his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret DeTimperly was born in 1584, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with Humphrey Hodges. She died on 28 February 1624, in her hometown, at the age of 40."},"et":{"1584–28 February 1624":"1584–28. veebruar 1624","1584–1624":"1584–1624","1596–1654":"1596–1654","1624":"1624","1654":"1654","Apr 1596":"aprill 1596","1596":"1596","1584":"1584","about April 1596":"umbes aprill 1596","28 February 1624":"28. veebruar 1624","Youlgreave, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","1666311, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Winterborne Came, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Winterborne Came, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1584–28 February 1624":"1584–28. helmikuuta 1624","1